SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR
TRUE, every point on the line connecting \(u\) and \(v\) is of the form \((1-s)u +sv\) for some scalar \(s\). Since S is a subspace, both \( (1-s)u\) and \(sv\) belong to \(S\), and so \( (1-s)u +sv\) belongs to S.
